"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-18-Paris-2024-Mayor-swims-in-Seine-to-ease-water-quality-concerns-1vkzW0qVXC8-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo swam in the Seine River with top Olympic officials amid water quality concerns ahead of the Paris Olympics.  This act was part of efforts to showcase the river's improved cleanliness. Organizers have invested $1.5 billion since 2015 to ensure the river is ready for the Games, constructing a water storage basin, renovating sewers and upgrading treatment plants.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"